<tr>
<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><small><b>Source:</b> <i>Scotland's Census Results Online</i><sup id="cite&#95;ref-111" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-111"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>108<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></small>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>Glasgow's population influx in the eighteenth and nineteenth centuries was related to economic expansion as well as internally generated growth with the vast majority of newcomers to the city from outside Scotland being from <a href="/wiki/Ireland" title="Ireland">Ireland</a>, especially the north western counties of <a href="/wiki/County_Donegal" title="County Donegal">Donegal</a>, <a href="/wiki/County_Fermanagh" title="County Fermanagh">Fermanagh</a>, <a href="/wiki/County_Tyrone" title="County Tyrone">Tyrone</a> and <a href="/wiki/County_Londonderry" title="County Londonderry">Londonderry</a>. In the 1881 UK Census, 83% of the population was born in Scotland, 13% in Ireland, 3% in England and 1% elsewhere. By 1911, the city was no longer gaining population by migration. The demographic percentages in the 1951 UK census were: born in Scotland 93%, Ireland 3%, England 3% and elsewhere 1%.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-ReferenceA&#95;28-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ReferenceA-28"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>27<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> In the early twentieth century, many <a href="/wiki/Lithuanian_people" class="mw-redirect" title="Lithuanian people">Lithuanian</a> refugees began to settle in Glasgow and at its height in the 1950s; there were around 10,000 in the Glasgow area.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-112" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-112"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>109<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Many <a href="/wiki/Italian_Scots" title="Italian Scots">Italian Scots</a> also settled in Glasgow, originating from provinces like <a href="/wiki/Frosinone" title="Frosinone">Frosinone</a> in <a href="/wiki/Lazio" title="Lazio">Lazio</a> and <a href="/wiki/Lucca" title="Lucca">Lucca</a> in north-west <a href="/wiki/Tuscany" title="Tuscany">Tuscany</a> at this time, many originally working as "<a href="/wiki/Hokey_pokey_(ice_cream)" title="Hokey pokey (ice cream)">Hokey Pokey</a>" men.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-113" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-113"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>110<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<table class="wikitable collapsible collapsed" width="100%">
<caption>Historical population and city limits
</caption>
